        h1 Privacy Statement
        p The following discloses the information gathering and use practices of the #[a(href="http://admissions.buffalo.edu") University at Buffalo Undergraduate Admissions website].

        h2 Information Gathering
        p Our policy is to collect no personally identifiable information about you when you visit our website unless you affirmatively choose to make such information available to us. However, our Web servers do automatically recognize some non-personal information. Specifically, when you visit the University at Buffalo Undergraduate Admissions website, we collect information regarding:
        ul
          li your Internet location (IP address)
          li the Web page from which you came to our site
          li the software (and its configuration) you use to visit our site
          li the dates and times you visit our site
          li the pages you visit on our site

        h2 Use of Information
        p We collect information to improve the functionality and content of the University at Buffalo Undergraduate Admissions website and to monitor its performance. We use the information gathered to adapt site content to user needs and to generate aggregate statistical reports that help answer questions about the usage and performance of the site or individual Web pages. Web server logs are retained only on a temporary basis and then deleted completely from our systems. We do not associate or disclose site usage by individual IP addresses — unless required by legally enforceable queries or for investigation of security breaches.
        p If you choose to share personal information with us, we will not sell that information to commercial entities. Some information must be retained for a designated period of time to comply with Federal or State records retention policies and may be released if required by freedom of information or public record laws. Most student information is confidential pursuant to the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA).

        h2 Security
        p The University at Buffalo Undergraduate Admissions website has security measures in place to protect the loss, misuse, or alteration of information under our control.

        h2 Contacting Us
        p If you have questions or suggestions about this privacy statement, the practices of this website, or your interactions with this site, please contact:

        ul.nobullets
          li: strong Mark A. Greenfield
          li Digital Strategist
          li 716-645-2811
          li: a(href="mailto:markgr@buffalo.edu") markgr@buffalo.edu

        h2 Disclaimer
        p The University at Buffalo Undergraduate Admissions website contains links to other independently administered sites within the University at Buffalo network and to some sites outside the “buffalo.edu” domain. We cannot be held responsible for the privacy practices or the content of such websites.

